cash crunch by printing its own "bond notes" will be valued in denominations of $2, $5, $10 and $20.&nbsp;The bond notes would reportedly be equivalent to the US dollar and would be backed by a $200m facility provided by the Afreximbank bank.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.